  "text": "Applied Rheology Volume 17 · Issue 5 where Q is the volumetric flow rate, and R is radius of the die. A short die of orifice type (L = 0.25 mm, D = 1 mm) was used for calculating the entrance pressure loss, DP ent . The short die has flat entry angle of 180° and an expansion region at the orifice exit. Diameter of the expansion exit section is eight times larger than the die diameter, which prevents the contact between the melt and the wall of the exit section of the orifice die. This ensures that the pressure readings represent only the effect of the die entrance [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The wall shear stress, t w , is calculated by:",
